Five staff members sustained serious injuries after taking a joy ride on 'the Super Slide' at the Sydney Royal Easter Show on Saturday night . 
  The slide was closed earlier in the night after heavy rain made it too dangerous . 
  A group of eight contracted workers broke into the slide after it was closed . 
  A 22-year old woman broke both her legs and a 60-year-old man suffered broken ribs and internal bleeding . 
  Officials said the slide 'runs way too fast in the wet' The slide underwent a safety check Sunday morning . 
 